[{"location":"#PlasmaDispersionFunctions.jl-Documentation","page":"PlasmaDispersionFunctions.jl Documentation","title":"PlasmaDispersionFunctions.jl Documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"PlasmaDispersionFunctions.jl Documentation","title":"PlasmaDispersionFunctions.jl Documentation","text":"CurrentModule = PlasmaDispersionFunctions","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"PlasmaDispersionFunctions.jl Documentation","title":"PlasmaDispersionFunctions.jl Documentation","text":"Modules = [PlasmaDispersionFunctions]","category":"page"},{"location":"#PlasmaDispersionFunctions.PlasmaDispersionFunctions","page":"PlasmaDispersionFunctions.jl Documentation","title":"PlasmaDispersionFunctions.PlasmaDispersionFunctions","text":"Calculate the plasma dispersion function\n\nprincipal(n, x) = x.^n .* exp(-x.^2) / √π\nintegrande(z, n, x) = P(x, n) / (x - z)\nresidue(z, n, x) = (imag(z) < 0 ? 2 : imag(z) == 0 ? 1 : 0) * im * π * principal(n, z)\nZ(z, n) = ∫integrand(z, n, x)dx + residue(z, n, x)\n\nExample\n\n  plasma_dispersion_function(0.0) ≈ im * √π\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"module"},{"location":"#PlasmaDispersionFunctions.plasma_dispersion_function-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{T, Unsigned}, Tuple{T, Unsigned, Any}} where T<:Number","page":"PlasmaDispersionFunctions.jl Documentation","title":"PlasmaDispersionFunctions.plasma_dispersion_function","text":"@docs     plasmadispersionfunction(z::T,power::Unsigned=UInt64(0),Z₋₁=missing)\n\nReturn the value of the plasma dispersion function This implementation includes the residue, which is easy to verify because Z(0) = im sqrt(π).\n\n...\n\nArguments\n\nz::T: the argument to the plasma dispersion function\npower::Unsigned=UInt64(0): the moment of the integral\nZ₋₁=missing: (optional) the value of the plasma dispersion function for\n\npower-1. If already calculated, passing this in saves some time. ...\n\nExample\n\n  plasma_dispersion_function(1.0)\n\nReferences\n\n[1] D. Fried and S. D. Conte, \"The Plasma Dispersion Relation\", Elsevier, 1961 [2] S.D. Baalrud, Phys. Plasmas 20, 012118 (2013) and put ν = -Inf [3] M. Sampoorna et al., Generalized Voigt functions and their derivatives,   Journal of Quantitative Spectroscopy & Radiative Transfer (2006),   doi:10.1016/j.jqsrt.2006.08.011\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#Index","page":"PlasmaDispersionFunctions.jl Documentation","title":"Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"PlasmaDispersionFunctions.jl Documentation","title":"PlasmaDispersionFunctions.jl Documentation","text":"","category":"page"}]
